        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:43PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Hoehne, or 19 miles north of Trinidad, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 30 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tyrone and Model.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
